search-interwiki-results-nrmwiki:
Search results description for Norman Wikipedia.

Note: the code "nrm" is non-standard and normally refers to another unrelated language.

The standard code "nrf" is assigned to continental (French) Norman but it encompasses several continental variants; other standard codes are assigned to the non-continental variants (Jerriais, Guernesiais) of Norman spoken in the Channel Islands.

This Wikipedia encompasses all Norman variants (with few differences that are mutually understandable). Only Jerriais has a standardized orthography, with a recent dictionnary officially supported in Jersey. Other variants are written with local adaptations which continue to change under the influence of the local dominant French or English language.

It has been suggested that this wiki be renamed using the "nrf" prefix, but this is still not implemented.
